creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 154 by Various.
Read in English by Shakira Searle; Ryan Finch; Tony Addison; Bruce Kachuk; Jacob Rabinowitz; Michele Fry; Sue Anderson; Newgatenovelist; David Wales; Kathleen Flanary; Sonia; Craig Campbell; Livia F.; Marwa Khalouf; Son of the Exiles; Phil Schempf; Thomas A. Copeland; Marissa Parker
This is a collection of 35 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for March 2016. It includes: After Love, by Sara Teasdale Annabel Lee, by Edgar Allan Poe Easter 1916, by William Butler Yeats The Exile, by Thomas Hood The Forsaken, by Thomas Hood Good Friday, 1613. Riding Westward, by John Donne Hymn to Proserpine, by Algernon Charles Swinburne Intimations Of Immortality, an Ode, by William Wordsworth Kin To Sorrow, by Edna St. Vincent Millay The Land Where Hate Should Die, by Denis A. McCarthy The Lee Shore, by Thomas Hood Love and Sleep, by Algernon Charles Swinburne Mercy’s Reward, by Sir Edwin Arnold Met, by Ella Wheeler Wilcox Of Shop Windows, by Thomas Burke The Partition of the Earth, by Friedrich Schiller Prisoners, by Hilda Doolittle The Rain, by William Henry Davies So-called Friendship, by J. Gordon Coogler A song, by Sir John Suckling Sonnet 61, by Michael Drayton Sonnet I (When you, that at this moment are to me), by Edna St. Vincent Millay Storm at Annisquam, by Madison Cawein Tamerlane, by Edgar Allan Poe The Tay Bridge Disaster, by William Topaz McGonagall To Althea, from Prison, by Richard Lovelace To An Old Mate, by Henry Lawson To One in Paradise, by Edgar Allan Poe Upon the Lines and Life of the Famous Scenicke Poet, Master William Shakespeare, by Hugh Holland Urbs Sacra Aeterna, by Oscar Wilde The Uses of Poetry, by William Carlos Williams Valgovind's Song in the Spring, by Laurence Hope When You are Old, by William Butler Yeats Windsor. Imprisoned in Windsor, He Recounteth His Pleasure There Passed, by Henry Howard The World, by Edwin Arlington Robinson For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
